          " Heroes Reborn was a 1996-1997 crossover story arc among comic-book
            series published by Marvel Comics. During this one-year, multi-title
            story arc, Marvel temporarily outsourced several of its most famous
            comic books to the studios of its popular former employees Jim Lee
            and Rob Liefeld. "  -- <a href=" http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heroes_Reborn" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heroes_Reborn</a>

         The "Captain America" and "Fantastic Four" sets were released prior to the
         start of the non-0-Day Weeklies, the "Avengers" set is the HiFi proper, and
         the "Iron Man" set was previously included in a 2012 Hitlist pack.

         The seemingly haphazard folder structure is due to this arc's emphatically
         "two-dimensional" structure: Sub-arcs stretch across all four titles during
         a single month just as much as within one title during successive months.
